# Database Scripts

- Put database scripts in `drizzle/` unless the existing project structure clearly requires a different location.
- Name future database scripts with a two-digit sequence prefix, for example `00_add_users_table.sql` or `01_backfill_user_roles.sql`.
- Every time a database script is created, add it to `drizzle/index_db.md` as an unchecked Markdown checklist item.
- Keep `drizzle/index_db.md` sorted latest first.
- The user will check off an item after running that script against the database; do not mark newly created scripts as run.
